                "title" : "Summary",
                "copy": "<p>The ability to move single atoms, the building blocks of all matter in the universe, is crucial to advancing nanostorage. In 2012, IBM announced the creation of the world's smallest magnetic memory bit, made of just 12 atoms. This breakthrough can transform computing by facilitating the development of devices that have access to unprecedented levels of data storage.</p><p>But even nanophysicists like to have a little fun. In that spirit, the scientists moved atoms by using their scanning tunneling microscope to make a movie, which has been verified by Guinness World Records™ as the world’s Smallest Stop-Motion Film.</p>",
